description:
Moby Dick (1956)

This classic story by Herman Melville revolves around Captain Ahab and his 
obsession with a huge whale, Moby Dick. The whale caused the loss of Ahab&#039;s leg 
years before, leaving Ahab to stomp the boards of his ship on a peg leg. Ahab is 
so crazed by his desire to kill the whale, that he is prepared to sacrifice 
everything, including his life, the lives of his crew members, and even his ship 
to find and destroy his nemesis, Moby Dick.

Director: John Huston

Writers : Herman Melville
